  <section class="brand-intro">
    <div class="brand-intro-inner">
      <h2>Viking in Southern California — What We Actually See</h2>
      <p>Viking has been the reference point for professional-grade home cooking appliances since the 1980s, and Los Angeles and Orange County have some of the highest Viking densities in the country. Bel Air and Beverly Hills estates, Newport Beach and Laguna Beach custom homes, Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village kitchens renovated in the last decade — Viking ranges and refrigerators are everywhere.</p>
      <p>The range igniter is the single most common Viking repair call we handle — roughly 40% of all Viking service visits. The symptoms are predictable: a burner clicking without lighting, or clicking continuously after the flame is already on. In most of SoCal, the first suspect is moisture in the igniter housing after cleaning. On coastal properties in Malibu, Newport Beach, and Dana Point, the longer-term cause is salt air corrosion of the electrode tips. In Ventura County and the canyon communities above West LA, wildfire ash contamination has become a specific, recurring cause we now flag explicitly on every service call in fire-affected seasons.</p>
      <p>The second most common call is the F02 oven temperature sensor on the range — quoted as a control board failure by other technicians more often than it should be. We test the probe first. It costs $82. The board costs $450+.</p>
    </div>
